tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria and tubular dysfunction. Urine is cloudy, brown, and ammoniacal, but no evidence of infection. HbA1c is low, excluding chronic hyperglycemia. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease; prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
